caller_intent: Kelly Robinson wants to add a vehicle to her existing insurance plan and confirm details for processing.
resolution_steps: Agent verified Kelly's account using her maiden name (Blackwood Robinson) and confirmed her address.
Kelly provided the VIN number of the vehicle to be added.
Agent clarified that the vehicle is not from a dealership and confirmed liability-only coverage was requested.
Agent verified Kelly's email address (Kmblackwo@gmail.com) for sending proof of insurance.
Agent confirmed the vehicle details (1997 Ford F-150) and assured processing.
knowledge_required: Insurance policy management (adding vehicles, verifying account details)
Handling customer account verification with name and address changes
Understanding insurance coverage types (liability-only vs. full coverage)
Email communication for proof of insurance delivery
summary: Kelly Robinson contacted Alliance Insurance to add a vehicle to her policy. The agent verified her identity, confirmed vehicle details (1997 Ford F-150), and clarified liability-only coverage. The agent will send proof of insurance via email to Kmblackwo@gmail.com. The call concluded with confirmation of processing.
